      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EYE SEE PHILTRA (4) has been racing well and maintained the momentum last time out when he scored at Echuca, leading and getting home by a head. Draws a few spots wider but the recent form is good enough to win a race of this calibre. SPIRIT OF SAHARA (1) led and faded last start but had some good form prior including a minor placing at Charlton two back and a Wagga win last month. Has a good record at this distance and should have no excuses from the inside draw. Worth another chance. INSIDE LEG (2) has been racing well from wider or second row draws including an easy win two back at Echuca. Led there so could take advantage of the low draw and won the only time he attempted this distance. OUR ART WORK (6) scored back-to-back wins before leading from this draw and fighting on for a close second at Mildura last time. Respect.",
